Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.29,0:00:05.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the rhythm of the wind, deductions become clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.25,0:00:07.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Figuring out the alibi trick!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.42,0:00:09.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The solution to the robbery case!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.05,0:00:11.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s real intention?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.34,0:00:13.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Recognizing that one truth,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.01,0:00:14.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A child with the mind of an adult,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.80,0:00:16.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.27,0:01:50.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The, the Detective Boys, went along with Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} to receive some festival dolls at Kanno{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s house.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.27,0:01:57.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, trying to purchase the scroll of the Thunder God, Tsumagari Mizutaka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.20,0:02:00.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the antique appraiser, Mie Yoshiharu{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, arrived at the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.03,0:02:03.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the grandmother Kanno{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} refused to sell it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.45,0:02:09.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However, while we went out shopping, the scroll vanished!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.75,0:02:17.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, look at this! The time on all of these faxes is 3:28 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.55,0:02:23.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means, before we arrived back here, the fax was running the whole time, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.52,0:02:29.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Would a burglar enter a room that's receiving messages, and risk being caught?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.06,0:02:35.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, a normal burglar wouldn't just leave the mistress's purse lying in the open in the bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.61,0:02:40.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And after looking in the bedroom, why didn't they look through all of the other rooms?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.45,0:02:41.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-True...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.45,0:02:47.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the strangest thing is, why did they only take the scroll?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.54,0:02:51.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the scroll is worth 20 million yen!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.63,0:02:56.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, you'd have to be a professional to know how much it's worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.34,0:03:02.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the burglar knew from the beginning that the scroll was here?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.80,0:03:03.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.31,0:03:08.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Except if they only wanted to take the scroll, they wouldn't need to go through the other rooms.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.39,0:03:14.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They went through the bedroom to create a crime scene and mislead the investigators.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.23,0:03:23.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which means the culprit doesn't have an alibi and knew they would have to talk to the police about the case at the crime scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.20,0:03:27.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Furthermore, that person has to know how much the scroll is worth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.29,0:03:36.00,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Festival Dolls Dyed in the Setting Sun
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.71,0:03:32.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Festival Dolls Dyed in the Setting Sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.67,0:03:33.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Part Two!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.09,0:03:42.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan. We've been in the tatami room...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.13,0:03:45.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There were only festival dolls there...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.31,0:03:48.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, look. Hasn't it changed a bit?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.39,0:03:52.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Before we went shopping, something was different.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.52,0:03:54.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where is there a difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.98,0:03:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't see anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.94,0:03:58.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! I see it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.61,0:04:03.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Emperor and Empress dolls have switched places with each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.45,0:04:05.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.20,0:04:09.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That isn't the only thing. Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}, do you have your digital camera?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.29,0:04:10.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.79,0:04:13.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.62,0:04:17.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look. Though it's a bit hard to see in the photo...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.84,0:04:21.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The other thirteen have also moved slightly, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.68,0:04:23.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's true...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.55,0:04:28.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely, when the culprit was trying to unhook the scroll,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.14,0:04:32.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They bumped into the stand and knocked the dolls over.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.73,0:04:38.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. I guess they were in a hurry, so they put the dolls in the wrong places.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.15,0:04:40.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, who is the culprit?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.90,0:04:41.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.86,0:04:43.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hurry up and tell us!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.57,0:04:47.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-Actually, the truth is, I don't know yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.58,0:04:49.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.54,0:04:51.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You looked like you knew everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.75,0:04:55.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But the dolls look so sad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.42,0:05:01.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Look, this doll looked happy earlier, but now it's different.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.59,0:05:05.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We tried so hard to set them up, and they were knocked over...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.59,0:05:07.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.14,0:05:13.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is someone who doesn't know how to order the festival dolls correctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.02,0:05:18.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means, the culprit is Tsumagari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, it can only be you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.98,0:05:25.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't you say that you don't have any daughters, and that you aren't interested in dolls, either?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.32,0:05:29.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! That's why you couldn't set them up correctly!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.37,0:05:31.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, just admit your crime!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.29,0:05:33.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.16,0:05:37.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, that's wrong. It wasn't Tsumagari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.38,0:05:40.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The real culprit is one of those two.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.13,0:05:44.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Those two are the only ones who could have done this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.97,0:05:46.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.38,0:05:49.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why would the dolls have to be set up again?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.06,0:05:55.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would look more like a robbery if they were just left lying on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.89,0:06:01.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, Tsumagari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, may we take a look in your apartment?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.65,0:06:04.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, with your permission.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.07,0:06:09.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand! Search as much as you want!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.07,0:06:11.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I'm telling you, you won't find anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.62,0:06:16.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, also, we will do a body check on you three as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.75,0:06:21.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You could be hiding the scroll underneath your clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.88,0:06:24.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then let's get going now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.63,0:06:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hopefully, we can get this done quickly before sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.51,0:06:27.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.88,0:06:32.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be! It's already this late...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.06,0:06:38.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But is Tsumagari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} really the culprit? I was only making a guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.39,0:06:40.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, I was following your lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.86,0:06:50.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, do you know who the culprit is?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.16,0:06:55.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry, I'm thinking about it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.08,0:06:58.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if we don't hurry, the stairs...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.42,0:07:01.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The stairs...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.88,0:07:05.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks, Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}! I've figured out the mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.92,0:07:09.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Really? So you know who the culprit is?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.13,0:07:11.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, thanks to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.55,0:07:14.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then 111 go call the officers back here!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.22,0:07:15.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.10,0:07:21.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!? You know who stole the scroll?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.27,0:07:24.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who figured it out?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.23,0:07:28.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You'll have to return to Kanno{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s apartment to find out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.28,0:07:30.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hurry, Officer!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.33,0:07:44.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.75,0:07:46.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So please, Mr. Sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.42,0:07:50.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a bit longer... Just a little...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.68,0:07:52.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.26,0:07:56.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've been waiting for this sunset.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.05,0:07:57.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.52,0:08:00.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks beautiful, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.64,0:08:03.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You seem to have an eye for these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.35,0:08:05.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.11,0:08:09.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, hurry and solve the case, and bring them here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.66,0:08:20.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sunset...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.12,0:08:24.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The world begins to turn red...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.08,0:08:25.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sunlight begins to fade...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.59,0:08:31.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who knows how many times I'll see it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.14,0:08:36.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This sad color.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.97,0:08:45.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well then, who managed to solve this case?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.44,0:08:47.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it have been you...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.61,0:08:48.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.11,0:08:49.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.53,0:08:52.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.28,0:08:55.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I've figured out everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.66,0:08:59.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit who stole the scroll, as well as the location of the scroll!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.79,0:09:02.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The hint is the festival dolls!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.04,0:09:09.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After taking the scroll and trying to run away, they knocked over the stand and tried to put the dolls back in order.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.30,0:09:15.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But when they were putting them back, they accidentally swapped the Emperor and the Empress.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.09,0:09:18.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the prime suspect would be Tsumagari{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.56,0:09:26.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wanted the scroll the most out of the four, and he's the only one who knows nothing about festival dolls!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.10,0:09:29.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're wrong! It's the other way around!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.19,0:09:29.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Other way?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.19,0:09:32.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, look closely at the festival dolls!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.82,0:09:39.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When all of us first came here, we set up the dolls without any mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.57,0:09:43.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From that time, everything stayed the same except for the Emperor and Empress!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.25,0:09:45.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.75,0:09:47.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.33,0:09:51.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the children set them up, I checked it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.09,0:09:57.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the culprit had bumped into the stand hard enough to knock over the Emperor and Empress,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.09,0:10:00.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,wouldn't the other dolls have been knocked over as well?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.85,0:10:03.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone who doesn't know anything about festival dolls
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.43,0:10:05.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,could not have ordered all of those correctly!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.48,0:10:12.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why would they make the mistake of switching the Emperor and Empress...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.23,0:10:14.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if it wasn't a mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.24,0:10:20.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if this arrangement of the dolls is the traditional Japanese way?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.95,0:10:22.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Traditional?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.91,0:10:23.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.29,0:10:32.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Japanese tradition states that left is ranked higher than right, and the left would wear dark clothes while the right wore red clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.75,0:10:39.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In the festival dolls, the older Minister of Right is on the left, and the young Minister of Left is on the right, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.43,0:10:47.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the emperor and empress, a male would be ranked higher than a female, so the man is on the left, while she's on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.19,0:10:53.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan, you're getting right and left wrong! The man's on the right!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.82,0:10:58.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because from the doll's perspective^the Emperor is on the left instead of the Empress.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.65,0:11:00.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's right...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.16,0:11:03.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But no one arranges them like this anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.95,0:11:05.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even all the stores do it the other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.91,0:11:08.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because it's Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.00,0:11:13.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When European culture entered the country,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.09,0:11:17.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the importance of the right over the left also came with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.63,0:11:22.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So most of the department stores in Tokyo arrange their festival dolls the other way now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.22,0:11:26.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow, you know so much for a boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.35,0:11:27.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yup!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.27,0:11:30.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I love studying ancient history books!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.61,0:11:35.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,U-Um, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.78,0:11:38.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have always been wondering...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.44,0:11:43.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How come you sound childish every time you talk to adults?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.53,0:11:46.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You sound sweet and cheesy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.83,0:11:48.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.16,0:11:50.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's kind of creepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.83,0:11:52.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.96,0:11:55.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll speak normally, okay? Normally!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.29,0:11:58.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I think it's really cute...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.38,0:12:00.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You always make such cute examples!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.39,0:12:06.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, who is the culprit, boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.72,0:12:07.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Uh... yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.72,0:12:11.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit is someone who arranges them by tradition.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.73,0:12:15.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that could only mean the grandmother Kano{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} or the appraiser Mie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.95,0:12:29.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When the grandmother was a young girl,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.70,0:12:32.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,people still set dolls the traditional way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.00,0:12:35.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The grandmothers hometown is Kyoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.25,0:12:39.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In Kyoto, families still set them up the old-fashioned way today.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.38,0:12:43.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was probably taught to set them up that way, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.30,0:12:52.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, Mie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} here, as an expert in many different ancient things, would know how to arrange the festival dolls from Kyoto.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.06,0:12:56.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He could have purposely set the dolls like this because he knew where they were from.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.73,0:13:00.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How would he know the festival dolls were from Kyoto?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.19,0:13:04.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The mistress Setsuko{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} told Mie{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.53,0:13:09.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it wouldn't be difficult to figure out the festival dolls were from Kyoto, because he could've known that as an expert.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.20,0:13:14.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then who's the culprit, and where is the scroll?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.04,0:13:16.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe you don't know it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.25,0:13:17.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I already know who it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.13,0:13:20.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because of the hint Ayumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} gave about the stairs!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.51,0:13:26.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Stairs... Could it be...!?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.80,0:13:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit climbed up the doll stand like a staircase, and then hid the scroll up there in the cupboard!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.06,0:13:38.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The dolls were probably moved slightly out of place as the culprit climbed up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.44,0:13:42.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, Genta{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, don't be so reckless!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.48,0:13:46.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's okay, because the scroll is most likely in this cupboard...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.37,0:13:49.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.41,0:13:50.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.70,0:13:52.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The scroll is in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.66,0:13:55.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit hid the scroll in this closet.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.62,0:14:02.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he moved the stand aside, some of the dolls fell off.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.30,0:14:07.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you go through the closet here, you can easily hide the scroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.72,0:14:08.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.68,0:14:13.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's nothing here but the boxes for the dolls...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.22,0:14:19.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't the culprit bump into the stand while running away?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.56,0:14:20.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.40,0:14:21.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The dolls didn't fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.48,0:14:28.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit had purposely lifted all the dolls off the stand to find a place to hide the scroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.45,0:14:30.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lifted them off?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.20,0:14:33.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then could the scroll be...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.54,0:14:37.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, help me take all these dolls off!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.66,0:14:38.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.92,0:14:49.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To hide a scroll somewhere convenient and hard to find...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.47,0:14:51.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.89,0:14:57.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Underneath the red felt of the Hina doll stand!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.89,0:14:59.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.73,0:15:03.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can't see it unless you take all of the dolls off.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.98,0:15:07.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No one would think of looking here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.69,0:15:11.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also, Ayumi, when you said the doll looked sad,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.78,0:15:16.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was because it was underneath this piece of wood.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.16,0:15:19.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I place the doll on the edge of the scroll,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.46,0:15:23.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he tilts forward and his expression looks different, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.92,0:15:28.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why it looked different!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.38,0:15:31.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why was the scroll placed upside-down?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.18,0:15:34.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The piece of wood at the bottom of a scroll is always heavier than at the top.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.10,0:15:37.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be obvious that the scroll was there even if the red felt was over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.10,0:15:42.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit hid the wooden pole behind the folding screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.85,0:15:44.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.44,0:15:47.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the culprit hid the scroll here, then that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.61,0:15:48.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.82,0:15:51.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The culprit was planning to pretend to c-lean up the dolls...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.49,0:15:54.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And take back the scroll after the police left.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.24,0:15:58.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Grandmother Kanno?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.08,0:16:01.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandmother Kanno?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.37,0:16:02.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.54,0:16:03.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.88,0:16:04.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.83,0:16:11.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You probably thought of hiding the scroll when we went out to buy groceries.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.34,0:16:14.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You messed up the room to make it look like a burglary!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.93,0:16:19.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And pretended to buy sugar...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.60,0:16:24.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So everyone would think that the scroll was stolen while no one was home.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.48,0:16:32.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She even thought of opening the balcony door to mislead us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.11,0:16:40.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They show that a lot on TV so she could have copied them?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.12,0:16:42.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.54,0:16:44.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why, Mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.12,0:16:47.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.00,0:16:50.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You wanted to claim the insurance money —
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.38,0:16:53.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's not like that. I didn't have any ill intentions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.26,0:16:59.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This scroll has been the Kanno's family's guardian for so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.43,0:17:01.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guardian?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.77,0:17:02.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.39,0:17:07.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was planning to hide the scroll until my son came home.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.94,0:17:12.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that I could explain the importance of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.32,0:17:18.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't want to repeat past mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.91,0:17:21.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Past mistakes? You don't say...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.33,0:17:23.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who figured it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.12,0:17:27.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It happened quite a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.29,0:17:32.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From the day I entered the Kanno family, I noticed two ancient scrolls,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.34,0:17:37.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,one of the God of Thunder and another of the God of Wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.39,0:17:41.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When he was still alive, my husband often said, "These two are the guardians of the Kanno family"...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.89,0:17:48.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I remember correctly, the two gods were guardian deities of Kanno, the Goddess of Mercy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.73,0:17:50.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When my son got married,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.06,0:17:52.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Our financial status was so dire.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.40,0:17:55.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I had to sell the God of Wind scroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.65,0:18:00.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I didn't tell my husband, who was on a business trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.32,0:18:05.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A few days later, I heard that my husband was in an accident at sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.83,0:18:10.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They told me he had come upon a huge storm and the waves capsized his boat...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.17,0:18:15.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As if the God of Wind created the typhoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.59,0:18:21.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that cursed scroll belonged to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.05,0:18:24.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and went through many hands before reaching mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.52,0:18:26.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't think it's cursed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.56,0:18:29.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Hina dolls used to be dolls put beside a child's pillow to protect her from bad spirits.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.31,0:18:34.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Every time I see a new stain on that scroll,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.48,0:18:40.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thank the Thunder God that he's taken the place of a Kanno family in meeting with something bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.16,0:18:44.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I will never sell this scroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.91,0:18:48.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.96,0:18:57.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And please do not ask for it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.59,0:19:00.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Er... Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.26,0:19:03.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.72,0:19:08.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now I know why you desperately want the Thunder God scroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.93,0:19:12.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You believe in the strength of the two deities so you want their protection for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.65,0:19:13.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.56,0:19:15.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of them is enough for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.69,0:19:19.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Pretend this never happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.03,0:19:20.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.74,0:19:22.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How disappointing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.24,0:19:28.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll be back later, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.08,0:19:32.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To show you how to properly take care of the scroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.05,0:19:41.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shall we go, too, Inspector?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.09,0:19:45.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll follow you back to the station so you can wrap this case up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.47,0:19:46.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Case?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.43,0:19:47.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.60,0:19:53.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two rooms were messed up and something was lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.61,0:19:56.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we called this a case,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.23,0:20:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then my boss will turn into the Thunder God.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.49,0:20:10.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With that aside, I'm sorry for putting you through all this trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.16,0:20:16.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll help you pack the dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.38,0:20:18.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, you can keep them!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.59,0:20:27.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't you think that my Hina doll was broken because it had an accident in my place?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.14,0:20:31.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm going to ask my dad to fix it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.10,0:20:33.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way, I can thank it for protecting me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.69,0:20:36.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, after all your hard worksetting the dolls up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.73,0:20:38.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, no...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.11,0:20:39.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.57,0:20:40.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yup!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.15,0:20:42.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.78,0:20:46.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Hina doll I really wanted was...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.20,0:20:49.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really, actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.50,0:22:24.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really... actually...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.76,0:22:26.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter to me, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.34,0:22:30.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You should hurry or you'll miss your chance.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.10,0:22:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's really pretty right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.31,0:22:38.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wow! It's amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.06,0:22:41.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sunset is beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:41.48,0:22:46.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see! You wanted to get the sunset in the photo!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.28,0:22:48.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan, sit here!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.40,0:22:52.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mitsuhiko, Haibara, and Genta, sit on the step below!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.08,0:22:54.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here's the camera
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.33,0:22:55.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.54,0:22:58.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why are we taking a photo in this direction?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:58.58,0:23:03.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The sunset as the background would look much nicer...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.17,0:23:05.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's okay, it's okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.42,0:23:07.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Smile, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.59,0:23:09.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.55,0:23:15.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The stairs look red and with the cream-colored elevator behind you...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.85,0:23:19.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems as if you are all Hina dolls!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.89,0:23:25.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, that means that Conan's the Emperor and I'm the Minister of the Left!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.52,0:23:27.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we're the three court ladies...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.28,0:23:29.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're one to talk!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.86,0:23:31.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.16,0:23:33.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Haibara{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, come and sit with me up here!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.99,0:23:36.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Move, Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.45,0:23:37.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stop-!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.83,0:23:45.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're the five male musicians...
